ŅTo Pam and Peter Norton who made
Dartmouth their adopted home and played
a major role in many of the towns
activities and organisations.
Peter was Honorary Treasurer of the
Regatta and Old Dartmothians Association
in addition to his many civic duties
always supported by Pam
"This town has benefited greatly from their
loyal commitment and wise stewardship""¶
